1
00:00:14,055 --> 00:00:17,308
All the windows in my house are covered.

2
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:20,228
I've put blackout curtains on all of them.

3
00:00:21,563 --> 00:00:23,440
Unless I open the curtains,

4
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:26,359
I can't tell if it's raining or snowing.

5
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:38,246
I stayed home most of the time.
I was out for less than ten days in total.

6
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:43,084
I think they call my condition

7
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:45,962
post-traumatic stress disorder?

8
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:51,384
And more recently, I've shown

9
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,428
defensive aggression.

10
00:00:57,807 --> 00:01:00,101
By the headboard of my bed,

11
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:02,479
I keep a 60-cm knife.

12
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:05,565
This is something
I can quickly grab and swing

13
00:01:05,648 --> 00:01:07,192
if there's an intruder.

14
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:09,986
I have an awl
and a bunch of other knives too.

15
00:01:11,988 --> 00:01:15,075
You just stab them in the side,
right where the lungs are.

16
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:16,701
Right under the ribs.

17
00:01:18,244 --> 00:01:20,246
When I wear my parka in the winter,

18
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:23,958
I keep an awl or a knife this big in it.

19
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:28,338
I hold it in my right hand,
tucked inside my pocket.

20
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:35,887
You know,
I've come close to death several times.

21
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:43,812
To be honest, I was desperate to survive.

22
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:03,832
It was past midnight.

23
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:08,920
After wrapping up a stakeout,

24
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:11,673
we were just waiting at the light.

25
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:13,174
SEOUL SEOCHO POLICE STATION

26
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:15,176
My pager buzzed. It was the station.

27
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,511
I had a guy get out of the car…

28
00:02:16,594 --> 00:02:18,930
KO BYUNG-CHEON
LEAD DETECTIVE OF THE CHIJON FAMILY CASE

29
00:02:19,013 --> 00:02:20,014
…and head into the office.

30
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:24,477
When I arrived,
the senior officer at the desk said,

31
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:26,104
"Hey, just who I needed. Get over here."

32
00:02:26,187 --> 00:02:27,939
OH HU-GEUN
DETECTIVE ON THE CHIJON FAMILY CASE

33
00:02:28,022 --> 00:02:30,024
So I asked him what was happening.

34
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:33,069
He said the complainant, Ms. Lee,

35
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:36,823
was high, talking nonsense,
and told me to take her away quickly.

36
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:40,160
He thought she was on meth.

37
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:43,955
Her statement was so wild
that it sounded like fiction.

38
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:49,210
She was talking about the murder.

39
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:52,046
But the whole story was hard to believe.

40
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,132
Not even a movie would go that far.

41
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:56,050
How could anyone…

42
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:58,678
She kept talking about chopping up bodies,

43
00:02:58,761 --> 00:03:01,723
shooting people to death,

44
00:03:01,806 --> 00:03:04,058
dismemberment, and burning the bodies.

45
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:08,062
So I asked her,
"Did you take any drugs or something?"

46
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:10,857
I even rolled up her sleeves
to check her arms.

47
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:13,526
I examined her closely,

48
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:16,362
but it didn't seem like she was on drugs.

49
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:17,447
Later on,

50
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:20,992
she confessed and said she shot someone.

51
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:25,455
She said she fired the gun,
after pressing it against their head.

52
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,374
I pointed the barrel…

53
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,753
LEE HYO-JIN
LAST SURVIVOR OF THE CHIJON FAMILY CASE

54
00:03:31,836 --> 00:03:34,380
It was probably right around here.

55
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:38,426
My finger was back on the trigger.

56
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:44,474
I pressed my finger,

57
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:47,185
and then…

58
00:03:57,362 --> 00:04:02,492
A six-member criminal gang,
equipped with a hideout and incinerator,

59
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:05,912
has been arrested for five murders
across the country.

60
00:04:05,995 --> 00:04:08,957
All suspects are in their early twenties.

61
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:13,044
With the goal of extorting one billion won
from the wealthy,

62
00:04:13,127 --> 00:04:16,339
they carried out a series
of indiscriminate kidnappings and murders.

63
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:21,552
Stop pushing!

64
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:26,182
Is it true that you ate human flesh?

65
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,267
It was just me.

66
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:29,852
I said I'm not a human.

67
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:33,231
-Why did you do it?
-To give up my humanity.

68
00:04:33,314 --> 00:04:35,191
Stand him up straight.

69
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:36,609
I'm not human.

70
00:04:37,193 --> 00:04:39,529
I regret not killing
everyone who deserves to die.

71
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:41,364
That I couldn't kill them all.

72
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:49,622
There were no stairs,
just a ladder set up.

73
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,541
When we climbed down…

74
00:04:53,918 --> 00:04:56,629
the scene in the basement
was beyond imagination.

75
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:58,756
PARK RAE-YONG
REPORTER, COVERED THE CHIJON FAMILY CASE

76
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,718
There was a furnace in the corner.

77
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:05,138
A huge one, made of concrete.

78
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:10,601
They essentially used it
as a furnace for disposing of bodies.

79
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:14,355
We didn't see much at first.

80
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:16,190
There was nothing but ash.

81
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:20,611
I grabbed the stick.
I think it's called a fire poker.

82
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:24,532
I dug around with it
and felt something rattling inside.

83
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:28,077
There were two skulls rolling inside.

84
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:37,712
It was pretty disturbing.

85
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:41,924
In my 30 years as a detective,
I'd never seen anything like that.

86
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:47,180
I was with the others
when I went down there,

87
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:51,601
but it still made my hair stand on end
and sent a chill down my spine.

88
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:56,272
It felt like I was on the set
of a horror movie.

89
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:03,363
It was truly beyond
what any human could ever imagine.

90
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:10,203
That place was like a murder factory.

91
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:13,873
MURDERS HAUNT SOUTH KOREA

92
00:06:14,582 --> 00:06:18,002
SOUTH KOREAN MURDERERS BLAME SPREE
ON THEIR ENVY OF THE WEALTHY

93
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:22,382
GRUESOME MURDERS PROVOKE
FRESH ROUND OF KOREAN SOUL-SEARCHING

94
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:28,304
This case was put to a stop when Ms. Lee,
who was kidnapped by the culprits,

95
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:31,307
managed a desperate escape,
narrowly avoiding death,

96
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,226
and reported it to the police.

97
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:43,986
It was either die there
or die trying to escape,

98
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:46,322
so I figured I might as well try.

99
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:51,994
That was how I tried
to make it up to the other victims.

100
00:06:53,663 --> 00:06:56,791
She had gone through
some horrific things herself.

101
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:59,335
After a difficult escape,
she reported everything to the police.

102
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,337
KO NA-MU
FORMER REPORTER, CEO AT FACTSTORY

103
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:05,508
That simple fact left
a strong impression on me.

104
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:09,720
That place was like a murder factory

105
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:13,558
where so many lives were taken.

106
00:07:13,641 --> 00:07:17,186
Just how did she survive all that
and make it out alive?

107
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:22,108
While I was in there,

108
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:26,070
I kept thinking, "Why me? Of all people?"

109
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:47,383
The only thing I did was try to survive.

110
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:50,219
I just wanted to live.

111
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:02,815
I AM A SURVIVOR
WHO TOOK A LIFE TO SAVE MY OWN

112
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:47,902
THE ECHOES OF SURVIVORS:
INSIDE KOREA'S TRAGEDIES

113
00:09:33,656 --> 00:09:35,449
How have you been?

114
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:37,410
It's been about 30 years now.

115
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,581
I guess for everyone else,

116
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:47,628
you could say it's been 30 years.

117
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:49,130
But for me…

118
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:52,216
I mean, 30 years may have passed,

119
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,011
but to me, it still

120
00:09:56,137 --> 00:09:58,973
feels like it was only a few days ago.

121
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:02,768
I feel like time stopped for me back then,
mentally and…

122
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:08,274
I'd like to forget about it.

123
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:12,445
I just wish I could forget and move on.

124
00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:18,951
Every detail of what happened there
is still vivid in my mind.

125
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:23,706
Which is why, from time to time,

126
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:27,585
I feel like my mind is still stuck at 27.

127
00:10:27,668 --> 00:10:29,170
It's 27 years old.

128
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:36,260
I was around 26 or 27 back then.

129
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:40,222
I had a part-time job.

130
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:43,643
I worked there for about a year.

131
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:52,318
I worked as a server at a restaurant

132
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:53,903
that served pork cutlets,

133
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:56,614
sujebi, kalguksu,

134
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:59,575
and dishes like omurice.

135
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:01,369
We served them for lunch.

136
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:08,668
Office workers from the area
would stop by for a beer at dinnertime.

137
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:13,547
That neighborhood had
a lot of office buildings.

138
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:20,054
At the time, live music was played

139
00:11:20,137 --> 00:11:25,643
by so-called bandmasters who would travel
from place to place to perform.

140
00:11:26,143 --> 00:11:27,061
So

141
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:31,357
we also had a bandmaster who was called in

142
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,693
every time a customer asked for music.

143
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:38,864
That was one of the reasons
I got to know him better.

144
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:45,121
He and Lee Hyo-jin were simply colleagues.

145
00:11:45,621 --> 00:11:49,667
One day, after work,
the two colleagues went for a drive.

146
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:54,797
They drove out to Yangsu-ri.

147
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:59,844
We went for a drive
and to meet up with friends.

148
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:08,894
We crossed the Paldang Bridge.

149
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,230
That's as far as I remember.

150
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:15,609
I kept staring out the window,
despite there being nothing to see,

151
00:12:15,693 --> 00:12:17,987
and suddenly, the car

152
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,073
came to an abrupt stop.

153
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:26,787
With a loud thud,
my head slammed into the dashboard.

154
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:30,791
I was like, "What the hell?"
and got really annoyed.

155
00:12:31,751 --> 00:12:34,003
When I looked ahead,

156
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:37,923
I saw a car blocking the road,
right across the center line.

157
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:41,510
Then some men suddenly sprang out
and approached us.

158
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:45,765
The window was open just a little,

159
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:49,101
and someone fired a gas gun at me
through the window.

160
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:53,939
Then he reached in to punch me.

161
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:57,359
It was hard enough to bruise me.

162
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:03,157
I found out later

163
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:06,619
that the bandmaster had been stabbed.

164
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:08,746
In the thigh.

165
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:13,751
It was actually pretty close to Gangnam.

166
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:17,880
They were waiting there
for any rich people passing by.

167
00:13:17,963 --> 00:13:24,094
So how do they immediately know
if their target is someone with money?

168
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:30,559
As the car goes by,
they check out the make and model.

169
00:13:32,561 --> 00:13:35,397
The two victims were in a Grandeur V6.

170
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:41,904
At the time, if you drove a Grandeur,
it meant you had money.

171
00:13:42,404 --> 00:13:43,739
So they kidnapped them.

172
00:13:43,823 --> 00:13:46,700
They'd shoot gas at their victims,
threaten them with knives,

173
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:49,036
tie them up, blindfold them,

174
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:51,580
and throw them into their car.

175
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:56,460
When they tied me up
and threw me into the truck bed,

176
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:57,753
I realized…

177
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:03,759
"These guys are no petty thieves."

178
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:07,555
I imagined that they might chop me up,
burn me, bury me,

179
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:10,850
or just dump my body in the water.

180
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:17,106
And as their truck was rattling
down the road,

181
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:19,358
I found myself thinking,

182
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:22,236
"So this is how I die."

183
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:26,699
"I just hope they keep me in one piece

184
00:14:26,782 --> 00:14:28,534
instead of chopping me up."

185
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,414
I think we were on the road
for a long time.

186
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:36,417
I fell asleep at one point.

187
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:39,587
I fell asleep in the vehicle.

188
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:46,552
But then
the truck suddenly stopped somewhere.

189
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:50,222
I heard a creak,
like some kind of gate was opening,

190
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:53,058
and then someone said,
"Hey, pull it into the garage."

191
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:59,523
With my eyes covered
and all my limbs tied,

192
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:01,984
someone picked me up and carried me.

193
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:08,866
And I think he carried me on his back
down the stairs like that.

194
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:16,540
I felt someone tap my face
and say, "Lift your head."

195
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:21,879
I tried not to look,
but before I knew it, I was looking up.

196
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:30,346
It only hit me
once my eyes were uncovered.

197
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:31,513
That place was…

198
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:35,809
It was like a prison.

199
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:39,980
There were steel bars and platforms
on either side of the cell.

200
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:45,653
That's when I gave up and thought,

201
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:48,364
"They are definitely going to kill us."

202
00:15:55,621 --> 00:16:00,292
DAY 1 OF THE MURDER FACTORY KIDNAPPING
SEPTEMBER 9, 1994

203
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:12,471
I'd been with the company about five years
and working harder than ever.

204
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:15,599
I'm from Gwangju,

205
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:19,228
and I was at my parents' place there
for the holidays.

206
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:24,024
But then I got a call from work.

207
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:28,278
A news team was heading
to Yeonggwang, Jeollanam-do.

208
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:32,741
I was told to join them
and supervise things on the ground.

209
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:44,086
The ridges of that hill
are still the same.

210
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,881
But that's all that remains.

211
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:49,383
Everything around it

212
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:52,302
has completely changed.

213
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:57,391
Now it's just a vacant lot
overgrown with weeds.

214
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:27,254
Cops came down from Seoul,
and the local police were there too.

215
00:17:27,337 --> 00:17:31,008
Dozens of media outlets,
each with about three to four people.

216
00:17:31,091 --> 00:17:34,636
TV networks, newspapers, and the locals.

217
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:41,310
Everyone had gathered around the house
they used as a hideout.

218
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:43,270
It was quite the commotion.

219
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,689
Totally chaotic.

220
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:54,782
This is the house in question.

221
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:58,077
They built themselves a hideout.

222
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:00,788
They painted it

223
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:04,041
pink and turquoise.

224
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:09,880
At first glance from the outside,
it actually looked really pretty.

225
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:15,928
The house itself is L-shaped.

226
00:18:17,262 --> 00:18:19,473
This right here is the garage.

227
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:21,517
Behind this shutter

228
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:24,394
is where they took
the victims' vehicles apart.

229
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:30,609
There's a metal panel under the parked car

230
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:33,362
that covers the passage to the basement.

231
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:37,825
Behind the shutter lies
a secret underground passage.

232
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:42,788
This is where the Chijon Family committed
gruesome murders and mutilated bodies.

233
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:47,876
The first thing you see
when you climb down the ladder

234
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,921
is a holding cell.

235
00:18:51,004 --> 00:18:52,840
With steel bars and everything.

236
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:04,017
It was basically like the holding cells
back at our station.

237
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:08,188
It was nearly identical to those cells.

238
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:10,023
We were also quite stunned.

239
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:10,941
You see…

240
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:14,278
that's what they did.

241
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:17,072
To the left of the entrance…

242
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:22,411
there was an incinerator in one corner.

243
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:26,248
They built a furnace with concrete,

244
00:19:26,331 --> 00:19:28,500
kind of like a brazier.

245
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:35,966
It was essentially a furnace
where they burned bodies.

246
